A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Hospitals – Parking for Patients
3 FOR the purpose of requiring hospitals in the State to offer parking at no cost for inpatients
4 and outpatients; requiring hospitals in the State to display signage notifying
5 inpatients and outpatients of the availability of parking at no cost; and generally
6 relating to parking for patients at hospitals.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Health – General
9 Section 19–308.12
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Health – General
15 19–308.12.
16 (A) (1) EACH HOSPITAL IN THE STATE SHALL PROVIDE PARKING AT NO
17 COST TO:
18 (I) EACH INPATIENT FOR THE DURATION OF THE INPATIENT’S
19 ADMISSION; AND
20 (II) EACH OUTPATIENT ATTENDING A SCHEDULED MEDICAL
21 APPOINTMENT FOR THE DURATION OF THE APPOINTMENT.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
